{"questionId":"9083599","questionHtml":"<p>During the nuclear fission of nucleus X into nucleus Y and nucleus Z, energy is released.&nbsp;The binding energies per nucleon of X, Y and Z are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>X</mtext></msub></math> , <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>Y</mtext></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>Z</mtext></msub></math> respectively. What is&nbsp;true about the binding energy per nucleon of X, Y and Z?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>Y</mtext></msub></math> &gt; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>X</mtext></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>Z</mtext></msub></math> &gt; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>X</mtext></msub></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>X</mtext></msub></math> = <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>Y</mtext></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>X</mtext></msub></math> = <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>Z</mtext></msub></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>X</mtext></msub></math> &gt; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>Y</mtext></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>X</mtext></msub></math> &gt; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>Z</mtext></msub></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>X</mtext></msub></math> = <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>Y</mtext></msub></math> + <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mtext>Z</mtext></msub></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9083599","referenceCode":"21M.1A.SL.TZ2.22","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"During the nuclear fission of nucleus X into nucleus Y and nucleus Z, energy is released. The binding energies per nucleon of X, Y and Z are BX , BY and BZ respectively. What is tr","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"22","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["E. Nuclear and quantum physics","E.4 Fission"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}